{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":43560,"duration_api_ms":43513,"num_turns":2,"result":"```json\n{\n  \"problem_framing\": \"The core artifact-metadata fix is fully approved: all four source files (service.rs, completion.rs, prompt_review.rs, final_review.rs) correctly source RecordProducer from InvocationEnvelope.metadata, cargo check passes, both targeted regression tests pass, and the full 86-test lib suite passes. Three pending amendments remain from the final review — all are cleanup of unrelated changes that were included on the branch: (1) two eprintln! debug-logging blocks in process_backend.rs lines 72-77 and 92-97, (2) unconditional --debug-file argument construction at lines 432-449 in process_backend.rs, and (3) the result symlink which is a local Nix build artifact. These must be removed to keep the branch cleanly scoped to the artifact-metadata fix.\",\n\n  \"assumptions_or_open_questions\": [\n    \"The two eprintln! blocks (lines 72-77 and 92-97) and the --debug-file argument setup (lines 432-449) in src/adapters/process_backend.rs are not present on master and were added as debugging scaffolding during development of this branch — removing them restores the master-branch behavior for those code paths.\",\n    \"The result symlink at the repo root is a local Nix build artifact that should be git-ignored or unstaged; removing it from version control does not affect builds or CI.\",\n    \"No other unrelated changes remain on the branch beyond these three items — the artifact-metadata fix itself requires no further modification.\"\n  ],\n\n  \"proposed_work\": [\n    {\n      \"order\": 0,\n      \"summary\": \"Remove eprintln! debug-logging blocks from process_backend.rs\",\n      \"details\": \"Remove the two eprintln! blocks at lines 72-77 and 92-97 in src/adapters/process_backend.rs. These unconditionally dump stdout/stderr content and result payloads to stderr on every JSON parse failure. They are leftover debugging scaffolding unrelated to the artifact-metadata fix. The surrounding error-handling control flow (the Err match arms) should be preserved — only the eprintln! macro invocations and their arguments are removed.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"summary\": \"Remove unconditional --debug-file argument from process_backend.rs\",\n      \"details\": \"Remove the debug_file path construction at lines 432-435 and the two argument pushes (\\\"--debug-file\\\" and the path) at lines 448-449 in src/adapters/process_backend.rs. This code unconditionally writes a debug log to runtime/temp/{invocation_id}.claude-debug.log for every Claude invocation, which is inappropriate for production. Removing it restores the master-branch argument list for the Claude CLI subprocess.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"summary\": \"Remove result symlink from version control\",\n      \"details\": \"Run git rm --cached result to unstage the result symlink (a local Nix build artifact pointing to a nix store path). Optionally add 'result' to .gitignore if not already present, to prevent future accidental commits of local build artifacts.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"summary\": \"Run cargo check and cargo test to validate cleanup\",\n      \"details\": \"After all three removals, run nix develop -c cargo check and nix develop -c cargo test --lib to confirm the branch still compiles cleanly and all 86 tests pass. This validates that the cleanup did not inadvertently break anything.\"\n    }\n  ],\n\n  \"readiness\": {\n    \"ready\": true,\n    \"risks\": [\n      \"The cleanup items are straightforward removals of additive debugging code and a build artifact — risk of introducing regressions is minimal, and will be caught by the post-cleanup cargo check and test run.\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"75992fe2-3d72-49fe-bb5d-d782c83162b2","total_cost_usd":0.18930100000000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tok